
** Commands

*** Command

  - $ rman target / catalog rman@test

  - RMAN> connect target /
  - RMAN> connect catalog rman@test

*** Backup

  - RMAN> backup database
  - RMAN> backup tablespace
  - RMAN> backup datafile
  - RMAN> backup archivelog
  - RMAN> backup current controlfile

*** Copy

  - RMAN> copy datafile
  - RMAN> copy current controlfile
  - RMAN> copy archivelog

*** Controlfile Autobackup

  - RMAN> configure controlfile autobackup

  1. With this feature restoring is possible without the RMAN
     repository - *disaster recovery*.

*** Rename Backupset

  - RMAN> backup device type disk format '/O2/tmp/rman/%d/%U'  
          backupset 1472 delete input;

